void

=======================================

Install

$ git clone https://github.com/jxdv/void.git
$ cd void/ && chmod +x void.py
$ sudo mkdir -p /usr/local/bin	
$ sudo ln -s $(readlink -f void.py) /usr/local/bin/void

=======================================

Usage

$ void -h
usage: void [-h] [-f FILE] [-r RECURSIVE] [-p PASSES]
            [-ee EXCLUDE_EXTENSIONS [EXCLUDE_EXTENSIONS ...]] -ow
            {zeroes,ones,random}

options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -f FILE, --file FILE  Path to file which will be overwritten
  -r RECURSIVE, --recursive RECURSIVE
                        Path to directory which contents of will be
                        overwritten recursively
  -p PASSES, --passes PASSES
                        How many times to overwrite the file
  -ee EXCLUDE_EXTENSIONS [EXCLUDE_EXTENSIONS ...], --exclude-extensions EXCLUDE_EXTENSIONS [EXCLUDE_EXTENSIONS ...]
                        File extensions to ignore
  -ow {zeroes,ones,random}, --overwrite-pattern {zeroes,ones,random}
                        Data overwriting pattern to use

=======================================

Examples

Run interactively

$ void -i

Overwrite with random bytes

$ void -f file.txt -ow random

Overwrite file 10 times with zeroes

$ void -f file.txt -ow zeroes -p 10

Recursively overwrite directory with ones

$ void -r target_dir/ -ow ones

Ignore files with .c and .o extensions

$ void -r target_dir/ -ow ones -ee .c .o

